{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cac3c0ae-046a-4020-ad16-64245607d8ce","content":"Here are the evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n### 1. **File I/O property function** (High impact) — Line 13\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading files via property functions runs during **every evaluation** (IDE open, restore, build, etc.). Move this to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs when needed.\n\n### 2. **Overly broad glob** (Medium impact) — Line 9\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" ... />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the entire directory tree on every evaluation. If large directories exist (e.g., `node_modules`, test data), this becomes very expensive. Narrow the glob to specific extensions or subdirectories, and add large dirs to `DefaultItemExcludes`.\n\n### 3. **Chained import depth** (Low impact) — `imports/`\n```\ncsproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThree levels deep is fine today, but this pattern can grow. Deep import chains add evaluation overhead. Keep imports as flat as possible.\n\n**Recommendations:**\n- Replace `File::ReadAllText` with a target that reads at build-time only.\n- Narrow `**\\*.*` to specific file types (e.g., `**\\*.txt`).\n- Add large directories to `DefaultItemExcludes` proactively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"83e2ff33-1b1d-4905-ae6c-c8ecf6471d33","outputTokens":354,"requestId":"C782:4701:1E632D:28060A:69FFDE88"},"id":"7ed732d2-e837-46b6-a03b-06a6a7a3b18e","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:25:40.084Z","parentId":"3b3cd69b-068f-4ed7-b06a-d802677a739a"}
